events.text: You made it to the waterfall!
You must be good friends if you were able to cooperate so well together!
I hope you had fun working together while you climbed your way up here.
Now, I won’t take much of your time here.
I would simply like to share some words of wisdom before you continue on with your journey.
The path ahead will be much longer than the one you just went through, so be prepared to fall down a few times.
And don’t blame each other for failing either, it’s just a natural part of the learning process.
Maybe drop down with them to help them get back to the rest of the group.
And feel free to try different paths or solutions, and discuss where you want to go or which paths you want to try next.
Working together is what got you here in the first place!
You should try to inspire and encourage each other to keep going, and don’t leave your friends behind if you’re ahead.
And of course, always keep talking to them!
Maybe even have a conversation while you’re navigating the path.
But I won’t ramble any further, you should know what to do by now.
